</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Short pet raid question</span><hr size=1> I have a short question about pets participating in raiding parties:<br>
<br>
The damage they do to the mob encountered, will it add up to the group's damage or is it more like a DS and therefore not adding up to the group's damage counter?<br>
<br>
Downburst <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uyarril.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Yarril</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#333333>(8/15/02 5:11:24 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=630.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Short pet raid question</span><hr size=1> In theory it would have to be counted for your group, unlike a DS.  Consider the smallest group possible (just you and the pet) killing some mob, where you are smart and use only a 7dmg DD spell to pull with (and to get all the xp, /applaud Verant for that change) and let the pet do all the rest of the work, maybe with a heal from you.  However, just when the mob is nearly dead, along comes a KSer, and nukes/backstabs/take-your-pick the mob, killing it.<br>
<br>
If the pet damage counted like a DS, the KSer would get the xp if they did more than the 7pts of DD damage you used to do the pull.  Since I'm pretty sure they wouldn't (but haven't actually tested this <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ) I'd expect the same thing would be scaled up to larger groups and raids.<br>
<br>
Hope that helps.  (if the KSer did get the xp in this fashion, it would definitely be a bug, but on the bright side, you could really PL people really easily too <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> )<br>
 <p><b>Yarril</b><br>57th Mage on <i>Xev</i>
